// =============================================================================
// Diakrisis Stage D.2 — 50 Foundational Theorems (10.T — 50.T)
// =============================================================================
//
// Source: A. Sereda, Diakrisis preprint, §03-formal-architecture/.
//
// The 50 foundational theorems span the metacategory structure
// (00 / 01), cohesion (02), fibration (03), gauge (04), modal
// interpretation (05), duality (06), model theory (07), cardinal
// analysis (08), and computability (09) of the Diakrisis canonical-
// primitive system.
//
// Each theorem is a `@framework(diakrisis, "...")` axiom placeholder
// citing the paper section. They form the structural baseline on
// top of the 13 canonical-primitive axioms of D.1, anchoring the
// downstream stages D.3-D.10.
//
// Theorem groups (paper sections):
//
//   Group 00 (10.T-15.T) — Metacategory structure: 2-categorical
//     setup, locally-small ⟪⟫, internal-closure derivation, ι-functor
//     existence, M-functor 2-natural-transformation properties.
//
//   Group 01 (16.T-22.T) — ι-embedding: faithfulness, fullness up
//     to gauge, image characterization, Yoneda compatibility.
//
//   Group 02 (23.T-26.T) — Cohesion: shape ∫, flat ♭, sharp ♯
//     adjunctions; cohesive structure on ⟪⟫.
//
//   Group 03 (27.T-30.T) — Fibration: Grothendieck fibration over
//     ⟪⟫ via M-image; categorical fibers.
//
//   Group 04 (31.T-34.T) — Gauge: gauge equivalence is Morita;
//     gauge classes as quotient 2-stack.
//
//   Group 05 (35.T-38.T) — Modal interpretation: M as a Galois-
//     connection lift to a modal logic; 4-2 modal axioms.
//
//   Group 06 (39.T-42.T) — Duality: M ⊣ A biadjunction precursor
//     (operator side; full biadjunction in D.7).
//
//   Group 07 (43.T-46.T) — Model theory: Lambek-Scott Syn ⊣ Mod
//     internal version; Diakrisis-specific Mod functor.
//
//   Group 08 (47.T-49.T) — Cardinal analysis: κ_1 / κ_2 size
//     bounds for ⟪⟫ + image(ρ) under (R5).
//
//   Group 09 (50.T) — Computability: Eff (Hyland) internal
//     interpretation foundation; ties to MSFS Theorem 8.6 (I_3).
//
// Each axiom carries an explicit anchor comment "Diakrisis §0X".
// Per-theorem detail expansion (full proof reconstruction) is
// the V2 work tracked under #181 V3 K-Eps-Mu — the axiom layer
// here establishes the trust boundary so downstream stages
// (D.3-D.10) cite specific 10.T-50.T results without re-deriving.
// =============================================================================

module lib.theorems.diakrisis.formal_architecture;

// =============================================================================
// Group 00 — Metacategory structure (Diakrisis §03/00, theorems 10.T-15.T)
// =============================================================================

@enact(epsilon = "ε_prove")
